  <discussion>Carex atherodes is a major wetland species in portions of the Midwest and West and
        becomes increasingly uncommon and local in the eastern portions of its range. It forms large
        clones and can tolerate deeper water than most Carex. Glabrous forms occur and seem to be
        more common in the western portion of the range.</discussion>
  <discussion>Carex atherodes rarely hybridizes with C. trichocarpa.</discussion>
